cs.CG, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the simplification of a geometric object, the Jacobi set, which is defined in terms of the gradients of two functions on a domain. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the Jacobi set and its simplification have applications in computer graphics and visualization. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category as the Jacobi set has been used in image segmentation and feature extraction. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper introduces a new algorithm for Jacobi set simplification. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of the Jacobi set in robotics and control theory.
